  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The XXttAAppppCCrreeaatteeSShheellll function saves the specified application name and
    application class for qualifying all widget resource specifiers. The
    application name and application class are used as the left-most
    components in all widget resource names for this application.
    XXttAAppppCCrreeaatteeSShheellll should be used to create a new logical application within
    a program or to create a shell on another display. In the first case, it
    allows the specification of a new root in the resource hierarchy. In the
    second case, it uses the resource database associated with the other
    display.

    Note that the widget returned by XXttAAppppCCrreeaatteeSShheellll has the WM_COMMAND
    property set for session managers (see Chapter 4).

